**Mortgage refinancing** (balance transfer) means moving your home loan to a lender offering a lower interest rate. A drop of even 0.5% on a ₹50 lakh loan can save ₹3–5 lakh over 15–20 years. However, refinancing involves processing fees (0.25–1%), legal charges, and sometimes prepayment penalties — this calculator finds the break-even timeline and net savings.
